{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3550185,"name":"$. Jazzwal","username":"Jazzwal","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jazzwal/{size}/188242_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-07T04:23:37.293Z","cooked":"<p>We are currently experiencing an issue where our robot sets its forward direction to -90 degrees randomly. Additionally, even after we use the reset Pose method from advantage kit which sets our ‚Äúzero‚Äù/forward direction for the swerve field relative, the robot still does this same random behavior. Has any other teams experienced any similar issues? We tried resetting the power wires to our Pigeon 2 and that did not work either <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/frowning.png?v=12" title=":frowning:" class="emoji" alt=":frowning:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"> We are a week 2 competition robot so any help would be greatly greatly appreciated <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=12" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"> please let me know if you need any clarifications <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slightly_smiling_face.png?v=12" title=":slightly_smiling_face:" class="emoji" alt=":slightly_smiling_face:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>
<p><em>update</em><br>
the robot drives robot centric to the April tag when the April tag is in view, even when the robot does not use the Limelight. Then, randomly, when the April tag is out of view, the limelight drives with the -90 degrees being forward.<br>
we took out our Limelight vision subsystem code and now the robot drives normally. what is going onüòÖ<br>
<em>also we are using both Limelight Helpers and Advantage Kit, could that be causing a conflict?</em></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-03-07T06:29:12.854Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":10,"reads":70,"readers_count":69,"score":64.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":494611,"topic_slug":"robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward","display_username":"$. Jazzwal","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49811,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward/494611/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3550205,"name":"","username":"mstatistics","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mstatistics/{size}/267172_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-07T05:03:27.547Z","cooked":"<p>Thats odd. Can we see the code? Does it also flip in advantage scope / logs or just driving?</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-03-07T05:03:27.547Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":56,"readers_count":55,"score":16.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494611,"topic_slug":"robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62510,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5892 Programming Lead"},"post_url":"/t/robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward/494611/2","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3550216,"name":"$. Jazzwal","username":"Jazzwal","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jazzwal/{size}/188242_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-07T05:23:51.834Z","cooked":"<p>This is the command we are using in the DriveCommands directly from Advantage Kit -</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  public static Command joystickDrive(
      Drive drive,
      DoubleSupplier xSupplier,
      DoubleSupplier ySupplier,
      DoubleSupplier omegaSupplier) {
    return Commands.run(
        () -&gt; {
          // Get linear velocity
          Translation2d linearVelocity =
              getLinearVelocityFromJoysticks(xSupplier.getAsDouble(), ySupplier.getAsDouble());

          // Apply rotation deadband
          double omega = MathUtil.applyDeadband(omegaSupplier.getAsDouble(), DEADBAND);

          // Square rotation value for more precise control
          omega = Math.copySign(omega * omega, omega);

          // Convert to field relative speeds &amp; send command
          ChassisSpeeds speeds =
              new ChassisSpeeds(
                  linearVelocity.getX() * drive.getMaxLinearSpeedMetersPerSec(),
                  linearVelocity.getY() * drive.getMaxLinearSpeedMetersPerSec(),
                  omega * drive.getMaxAngularSpeedRadPerSec());
          boolean isFlipped =
              DriverStation.getAlliance().isPresent()
                  &amp;&amp; DriverStation.getAlliance().get() == Alliance.Red;
          drive.runVelocity(
              ChassisSpeeds.fromFieldRelativeSpeeds(
                  speeds,
                  isFlipped
                      ? drive.getRotation().plus(new Rotation2d(Math.PI))
                      : drive.getRotation()));
        },
        drive);
  }
</code></pre>
<p>This is how we call this command in the robotContainer -</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">   drive.setDefaultCommand(
        DriveCommands.joystickDrive(
            drive, () -&gt; xbox0.getLeftY(), () -&gt; xbox0.getLeftX(), () -&gt; -xbox0.getRightX()));
</code></pre>
<p>This is how we set our ‚Äúzero‚Äù -</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  xbox0
        .b()
        .onTrue(
            Commands.runOnce(
                    () -&gt;
                        drive.setPose(
                            new Pose2d(drive.getPose().getTranslation(), new Rotation2d())),
                    drive)
                .ignoringDisable(true));
</code></pre>
<p>Our yaw does not reset on our gyro as we are just resetting the Pose (which as I understand it just resets the robot‚Äôs odometry and not the gyro itself) so our SmartDashboard just shows the gyro accumulating in value. Should we be resetting the gyro‚Äôs ‚Äúzero‚Äù instead? Please let me know if you need more clarification/more specific code from elsewhere in our repo <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=12" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-03-07T05:24:21.034Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":10.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494611,"topic_slug":"robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward","display_username":"$. Jazzwal","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":62510,"username":"mstatistics","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mstatistics/{size}/267172_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49811,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward/494611/3","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3550221,"name":"$. Jazzwal","username":"Jazzwal","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jazzwal/{size}/188242_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-07T05:45:34.432Z","cooked":"<p>Now the robot is setting field relative forward to -90 and then 90 (with our zero being ‚Äúdown field‚Äù). Might just be pre competition jitters‚Äã:sweat_smile: but so far we haven‚Äôt found any rhyme or reason to the changing of the ‚Äúforward‚Äù direction. So far there is nothing in code that is being called while our joystick drive is running, so I am very much confused‚Äã:sweat_smile: please let me know if there is anything I can clarify or test for you guys <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=12" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-03-07T05:45:34.432Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":32,"readers_count":31,"score":16.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":494611,"topic_slug":"robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward","display_username":"$. Jazzwal","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49811,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward/494611/4","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3550258,"name":"$. Jazzwal","username":"Jazzwal","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jazzwal/{size}/188242_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-07T08:11:02.625Z","cooked":"<p>After 3 hours of testing we have concluded that this is caused somehow by our usage of both LimelightHelpers and AdvantageKit together. When we are viewing an April Tag, the robot moves in Robot Centric in reference to the April tag it sees, regardless of whether our alignment command is being used. We removed the functionality of the AdvantageKit vision features and are just using the LimelightHelpers - making our robot do what we want it to do (for now at leastüòÖ)</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2025-03-07T08:11:02.625Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":5.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":494611,"topic_slug":"robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward","display_username":"$. Jazzwal","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49811,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/robot-field-relative-randomly-setting-90-degrees-as-forward/494611/5","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true}],"stream":[3550185,3550205,3550216,3550221,3550258]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,150]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":495246,"title":"Robot drives itself immediately w